 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Notebook 04 — Multi-Task ChemBERTa\n",
    "## Joint ADMET Prediction Across Multiple Endpoints\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Shahid Afridi Laskar  \n",
    "**Project:** ChemBERTa-ADMET  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "In drug discovery, compounds must simultaneously satisfy multiple ADMET criteria — a molecule with excellent BBB permeability but poor solubility is not a viable lead. Multi-task learning allows a single model to jointly optimise for all endpoints, with the potential for positive transfer between related tasks.\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements a `ChemBERTaMultiTask` model with separate heads for:\n",
    "- BBBP (classification)\n",
    "- ESOL solubility (regression)\n",
    "- ClinTox toxicity (classification)\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append('..')\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, Dataset\n",
    "from torch.optim import AdamW\n",
    "from transformers import get_linear_schedule_with_warmup\n",
    "import deepchem as dc\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data_utils import dataset_to_dataframe\n",
    "from src.models import ChemBERTaMultiTask, get_tokenizer, tokenize_smiles, multitask_loss\n",
    "from src.evaluate import classification_metrics, regression_metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "DEVICE = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'\n",
    "print(f'Device: {DEVICE}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load and Align Datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "Multi-task training requires aligned batches. We use a union approach: each compound may have labels for some tasks but not others (missing labels masked as NaN)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tokenizer = get_tokenizer()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load datasets\n",
    "tasks_bbbp, (tr_bbbp, va_bbbp, te_bbbp), _ = dc.molnet.load_bbbp(\n",
    "    featurizer=dc.feat.DummyFeaturizer(), splitter='scaffold')\n",
    "\n",
    "tasks_esol, (tr_esol, va_esol, te_esol), _ = dc.molnet.load_delaney(\n",
    "    featurizer=dc.feat.DummyFeaturizer(), splitter='scaffold')\n",
    "\n",
    "tasks_ct, (tr_ct, va_ct, te_ct), _ = dc.molnet.load_clintox(\n",
    "    featurizer=dc.feat.DummyFeaturizer(), splitter='scaffold')\n",
    "\n",
    "df_bbbp = dataset_to_dataframe(tr_bbbp, tasks_bbbp).rename(columns={'p_np': 'bbbp'})\n",
    "df_esol = dataset_to_dataframe(tr_esol, tasks_esol).rename(columns={tasks_esol[0]: 'esol'})\n",
    "df_ct   = dataset_to_dataframe(tr_ct,   tasks_ct).rename(columns={'CT_TOX': 'clintox'})[['smiles','clintox']]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge on SMILES (outer join — NaN where compound not in dataset)\n",
    "df_merged = df_bbbp[['smiles','bbbp']].merge(\n",
    "    df_esol[['smiles','esol']], on='smiles', how='outer').merge(\n",
    "    df_ct[['smiles','clintox']], on='smiles', how='outer')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Merged dataset: {df_merged.shape}')\n",
    "print(df_merged.isna().sum())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Multi-Task Dataset Class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class MultiTaskSMILESDataset(Dataset):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Dataset for multi-task learning with NaN-masked labels.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __init__(self, smiles_list, labels_df, tokenizer, max_length=128):\n",
    "        self.encodings = tokenize_smiles(smiles_list, tokenizer, max_length)\n",
    "        self.labels = labels_df.values.astype(float)  # shape (n, n_tasks)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\n",
    "        return len(self.labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n",
    "        item = {k: v[idx] for k, v in self.encodings.items()}\n",
    "        item['labels'] = torch.tensor(self.labels[idx], dtype=torch.float32)\n",
    "        return item\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "smiles_list = df_merged['smiles'].tolist()\n",
    "label_cols  = ['bbbp', 'esol', 'clintox']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simple 80/20 split for this notebook\n",
    "split = int(0.8 * len(smiles_list))\n",
    "train_ds = MultiTaskSMILESDataset(smiles_list[:split], df_merged[label_cols].iloc[:split], tokenizer)\n",
    "val_ds   = MultiTaskSMILESDataset(smiles_list[split:], df_merged[label_cols].iloc[split:], tokenizer)\n",
    "\n",
    "train_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=16, shuffle=True)\n",
    "val_loader   = DataLoader(val_ds,   batch_size=16, shuffle=False)\n",
    "print(f'Train: {len(train_ds)}, Val: {len(val_ds)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Build Multi-Task Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "task_configs = [\n",
    "    {'name': 'bbbp',    'task_type': 'classification', 'n_classes': 1},\n",
    "    {'name': 'esol',    'task_type': 'regression',     'n_classes': 1},\n",
    "    {'name': 'clintox', 'task_type': 'classification', 'n_classes': 1},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "model_mt = ChemBERTaMultiTask(task_configs=task_configs, dropout=0.1)\n",
    "model_mt = model_mt.to(DEVICE)\n",
    "print(f'Multi-task model parameters: {sum(p.numel() for p in model_mt.parameters()):,}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata":",
   "source": [
    "## 4. Training Loop"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "EPOCHS = 3  # increase for full training\n",
    "optimizer = AdamW(model_mt.parameters(), lr=2e-5, weight_decay=0.01)\n",
    "total_steps = len(train_loader) * EPOCHS\n",
    "scheduler = get_linear_schedule_with_warmup(\n",
    "    optimizer, num_warmup_steps=int(0.1*total_steps), num_training_steps=total_steps)\n",
    "\n",
    "task_name_map = {cfg['name']: i for i, cfg in enumerate(task_configs)}\n",
    "history = {'train_loss': [], 'val_loss': []}\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n",
    "    model_mt.train()\n",
    "    train_losses = []\n",
    "    for batch in tqdm(train_loader, desc=f'Epoch {epoch+1}'):\n",
    "        input_ids = batch['input_ids'].to(DEVICE)\n",
    "        attn_mask = batch['attention_mask'].to(DEVICE)\n",
    "        label_tensor = batch['labels'].to(DEVICE)\n",
    "\n",
    "        predictions = model_mt(input_ids, attn_mask)\n",
    "        targets = {cfg['name']: label_tensor[:, i] for i, cfg in enumerate(task_configs)}\n",
    "\n",
    "        loss = multitask_loss(predictions, targets, task_configs)\n",
    "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "        loss.backward()\n",
    "        torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model_mt.parameters(), 1.0)\n",
    "        optimizer.step()\n",
    "        scheduler.step()\n",
    "        train_losses.append(loss.item())\n",
    "\n",
    "    avg_train = np.mean(train_losses)\n",
    "    history['train_loss'].append(avg_train)\n",
    "    print(f'Epoch {epoch+1}: train_loss = {avg_train:.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Training complete.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "Multi-task ChemBERTa learns shared molecular representations across classification and regression endpoints simultaneously. Key advantages:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Single inference pass** returns all ADMET properties — practical for virtual screening pipelines\n",
    "2. **Positive transfer** between related tasks (e.g., solubility and BBB permeability share physicochemical drivers)\n",
    "3. **NaN masking** allows training on incomplete labels — real-world drug discovery datasets rarely have complete coverage\n",
    "\n",
    "**Next:** `05_results_analysis.ipynb` — Full benchmark comparison and figures."
   ]
  }
 ],
